elephants.name: Queenie
elephants.note: A captive female Asian which was noted in the late 1950s and early 1960s for waterskiing for entertainment.

elephants.name: Tuffi
elephants.note: A female circus elephant that became famous in Germany during 1950 when she accidentally fell into the River Wupper, and survived.

elephants.name: Topsy
elephants.note: Killed a spectator who burned her trunk with a lit cigar. In 1903 the owners of a Coney Island park where she ended up publicly executed her via poison, electrocution, and strangling. The Edison Manufacturing movie company shot a film of the execution called Electrocuting an Elephant.
